card.note: Jim Vozzella is one of the nicest and sweetest people on Earth. A hug from him can totally make your day.
card.author: Ilana Gordon

card.note: Whether its been days, weeks or months, hanging out with you seems like no time is lost. That speaks to the strength of our friendship and thus why you'll always be an important part of my life./R/RI wish you the best and happiest of birthdays!
card.author: Joey C

card.note: My most favorite thing about Jim is, he will go out of his way for anybody. From moving you out of your apartment or helping you get married, he never hesitates to be there for you. And put a beer in front of him, he will let you talk his ear off till 2AM. Love U Jim!
card.author: Amy Zeier

card.note: This card isn't big enough. I love that you're patient and kind and giving. You see the best in people and push me to be a better person by example. And you buy me Cheez-Its on bad days. And keep me from eating Cheez-Its on good ones. I love you!
card.author: LOVE Maureen

card.note: Jim, who could ask for a better friend? There's no one else I'd rather talk to on the phone while we're both pooping. Congratulations on surviving this long. May the odds be ever in your favor.
card.author: Tony Lentino

card.note: Being part of AG was one of the coolest and most fun things I've ever done. I consider every member of our group to be my friend but I know you, Jim, are the guy that brought me in and brought me back. I will always be grateful to have shared the stage with you & AG.
card.author: Mark Russell (aka Mr. Brennan)

card.note: Jimmy you are a good person and that makes so proud of you. Love and Happy Birthday.
card.author: Dad

card.note: Jim is a kind, thoughtful, and devoted person. He goes to great lengths to be supportive, whether performing for me when I was sick (& he had a fever), or painting while I was stressed and out of town. I know I can always count on Jim, and I'm lucky to call him a friend
card.author: Lillie (and Laugh Out Loud!)

card.note: Jim, You always have a smile on your face and that smile is contagious.
card.author: Harz

card.note: Gosh Jim Vozzella, you are a sweet man and your attitude stays positive no matter what./R/RThis does not include when you are cut off while driving. /R/REverything else though, so sweet!
card.author: Sean Sullivan

card.note: Jim has the most disproportionately long arms of anyone I know. I'm pretty sure he stole them from a taller person and had them grafted on in a lab in a hollow volcano somewhere. Oh, yeah, and he's also one of the most warm and generous people, blah blah blah, etc
card.author: Ed Schweitzer

card.note: Jim was ahead of the craft beer scene by like 5 years. He also discovered Stonewood. He's got a great heart and is hilarious. A true good friend that I wish I saw more of.
card.author: Marc Beth

card.note: My favorite memory of James is having to pick him up from behind a 7 11 dumpster
card.author: Anthony Vozzella

card.note: The thing I love most about my brother is he would be at my side if I ever needed him.
card.author: Anthony Vozzella

card.note: Do you know why you are gay?.../RYou just got a box of affirmations for your birthday.
card.author: Anthony Vozzella

card.note: We will always share a love for Prince and an utter hate for SoCo...
card.author: Heather Vozzella

card.note: RANCH.
card.author: Heather vozzella

card.note: Dear James/RHappy Birthday to a great son. I am very proud of you. You have grown to be a good and caring person. Always stay like that./R Love Mom
card.author: Peggy Vozzella

card.note: Jim, you rock! It is a true delight interacting with you both on and off the stage. You sir, are a wonderful gentleman.
card.author: Steven from New Zealand

card.note: You're a quality person, James./R/RMay the world endeavour to match your standard./R/RAlso, happy birthday.
card.author: jin
